senses.sense_definition: A wheeled motor vehicle used for transportation, typically having four wheels and powered by an internal combustion engine or electric motor.

examples.text: He drove his <w>car</w> to the theatre.
She is thinking about buying a brand new <w>car</w>.

senses.sense_definition: A vehicle designed to run on rails, used to carry passengers or cargo in a train.

examples.text: The conductor coupled the <w>cars</w> to the locomotive.
From the frontmost <w>car</w> of the subway, he filmed the tunnel.

senses.sense_definition: The passenger-carrying part of an amusement park ride, such as a Ferris wheel.

examples.text: The most exciting part of riding a Ferris wheel is when your <w>car</w> goes over the top.
The children had fun crashing their bumper <w>cars</w> into each other.

senses.sense_definition: The moving chamber of an elevator that carries passengers or freight.

examples.text: The technician came to fix the <w>car</w> of the express elevator.
We were stuck inside the elevator <w>car</w> for ten minutes.

senses.sense_definition: The compartment of a balloon or airship that holds passengers and equipment.

examples.text: I stepped into the <w>car</w> of the balloon to begin the journey.
The pilot navigated the airship from the control <w>car</w>.

senses.sense_definition: A wheeled vehicle drawn by a horse or other animal; a chariot.

examples.text: The king rode in a golden <w>car</w> drawn by white horses.
Aphrodite is represented as riding in a <w>car</w> drawn by sparrows.

senses.sense_definition: The first element of a list in the Lisp programming language.

examples.text: The <w>car</w> of the list (a b c) is the element a.

senses.sense_definition: Initialism of the Central African Republic.

examples.text: Decades of conflict in <w>CAR</w> have caused instability in the region.
The delegation visited <w>CAR</w> to discuss peace treaties.

senses.sense_definition: A Nicobarese language spoken in the Nicobar Islands of India.

examples.text: The linguist is documenting the grammar of <w>Car</w>.
Native speakers of <w>Car</w> live primarily in the Nicobar Islands.
